Now lets do some visualizations on the dataset with respect to the class variable

# Function to create boxplots
# Create a copy of the dataset for visualization
diabetes_visualization <- diabetes

# Convert CLASS to a factor with specific levels order
diabetes_visualization$CLASS <- factor(diabetes_visualization$CLASS, levels = c("N", "P", "Y"))
create_boxplot <- function(variable) {
  ggplot(diabetes, aes(x = CLASS, y = !!sym(variable), fill = CLASS)) +
    geom_boxplot() +
    labs(title = paste("Boxplot of", variable, "by CLASS")) +
    theme_minimal()
}

# Function to create density plots
create_density_plot <- function(variable) {
  ggplot(diabetes_visualization, aes(x = !!sym(variable), fill = CLASS)) +
    geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
    labs(title = paste("Density Plot of", variable, "by CLASS")) +
    theme_minimal()
}

# List of numerical variables for visualization
numerical_variables <- c("AGE", "Urea", "Cr", "HbA1c", "Chol", "TG", "HDL", "LDL", "VLDL", "BMI")

# Create and display boxplots

Research Question 1 1) a) How do various factors contribute to the likelihood of patients being diagnosed with diabetes, as indicated by the CLASS variable. b) Identify and analyze the most influential features identified by the decision tree model. Assess the comparative effectiveness of a decision tree model against logistic regression in determining the presence or absence of a medical condition.
